WOL
===============================

Author: Timo Furrer <timo.furrer@gmx.ch>
License: GPL
Copyright (C) 2011 by Timo Furrer

===============================

With this smart C program you can send a wol magic packet to a mac address.

Using
==============================
Usage: ./wol.c [-r remoteaddr] [-f filename1, ...|mac1, ...]

You can either pass some mac addresses or you can pass with the option f some filenames contains a mac address on each line to wake up.
With the option r you can specify the remote ip address. The default value is 255.255.255.255
